      What is Tom Cruise religion?
      Scientology
      Cruise was converted to Scientology by his first wife Mimi Rogers in 1986, becoming an outspoken advocate for the Church of Scientology in the 2000s. His involvement in the organization was leaked by the tabloid Star in 1990, and he publicly admitted to following Scientology in a 1992 interview with Barbara Walters.

      About

      Description

      Tom Cruise is an American actor and producer. One of the world's highest-paid actors, he has received various accolades, including an Honorary Palme d'Or and three Golden Globe Awards, in addition to nominations for four Academy Awards. Wikipedia
      Born: July 3, 1962 (age 60 years), Syracuse, New York, United States
      Spouse: Katie Holmes (m. 2006–2012), Nicole Kidman (m. 1990–2001), Mimi Rogers (m. 1987–1990)
      Height: 1.7 m
      Children: Suri Cruise, Connor Cruise, Isabella Jane Cruise
      Upcoming movies: Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part One, Mission: Impossible – Dead Reckoning Part Two
      Parents: Thomas Mapother III, Mary Lee Pfeiffer
